    {
      "id": "PopularPost69404",
      "post_content": "I see no reason to complain about a 1 drop that will kill off [Serra Angel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Serra Angel) no problem. It doesn't need to be an instant. If it was, no duh it would be better than [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt), but bolt is the epitome of red and is perfectly balanced, so why do we need a card that is clearly better than it in all aspects? People worry about Power Creep in this game, saying Wizards is making cards too powerful, but they do it to please the same fans that complain that Flame Slash should have been an instant. Making a card more powerful than \\ Lightning Bolt is asking for power creep, not balance. Bolt is good enough; if you want another bolt, then hope for a reprint. But if you expect a card to come out that is better than it in every way, you're asking for power creep to dominate all new sets.",
      "posted_by": "sarroth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost69404\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_post\">I see no reason to complain about a 1 drop that will kill off <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Serra Angel\">Serra Angel</a> no problem.  It doesn't need to be an instant.  If it was, no duh it would be better than <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a>, but bolt is the epitome of red and is perfectly balanced, so why do we need a card that is clearly better than it in all aspects?  People worry about Power Creep in this game, saying Wizards is making cards too powerful, but they do it to please the same fans that complain that Flame Slash should have been an instant.  Making a card more powerful than \\ Lightning Bolt is asking for power creep, not balance.  Bolt is good enough; if you want another bolt, then hope for a reprint.  But if you expect a card to come out that is better than it in every way, you're asking for power creep to dominate all new sets.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl06_reportAbuseLink\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy20957\">sarroth</span>\r\n                                (4/28/2010 8:23:05 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class