    {
      "id": "PopularPost221240",
      "post_content": "1) Instant-speed removal is \\*very convenient\\* because it can easily generate 2x1 in response to enchants, [giant growth](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=giant growth)-style cards, or other pumpers. it also allows you to cast it in the other player's turn, when you have the most information of what he's going to do, so you can take better decisions.  \n2) Not being able to hit players is... well, lame. As creature removal it's ok, but it's not fantastic; imho, it's just a bad-quality [Path to Exile](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Path to Exile)/[Swords to Plowshares](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares)/[Doom Blade](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doom Blade)/[Go for the throat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Go for the throat). But it's in red so it's ok, it's still one of the best creature-removal spells in red.  \n3) The comparison to [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt) is, imho, completely dummy. Lightning wins hands down. Still, the bolt is a versatile and powerful card that sets the \"gold standard\" for direct damage. The only case in which this would be preferred to the bolt is in a meta crowded with 4-toughness... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "ninjabear",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost221240\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">1) Instant-speed removal is *very convenient* because it can easily generate 2x1 in response to enchants, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=giant growth\">giant growth</a>-style cards, or other pumpers. it also allows you to cast it in the other player's turn, when you have the most information of what he's going to do, so you can take better decisions.<br/>2) Not being able to hit players is... well, lame. As creature removal it's ok, but it's not fantastic; imho, it's just a bad-quality <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Path to Exile\">Path to Exile</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares\">Swords to Plowshares</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doom Blade\">Doom Blade</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Go for the throat\">Go for the throat</a>. But it's in red so it's ok, it's still one of the best creature-removal spells in red.<br/>3) The comparison to <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a> is, imho, completely dummy. Lightning wins hands down. Still, the bolt is a versatile and powerful card that sets the \"gold standard\" for direct damage. The only case in which this would be preferred to the bolt is in a meta crowded with 4-toughness... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 221240)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\